ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Now I see the data layer for wapi, wcity, wcore, wmix all provide `ev
entbus.Config` and `eventbus.StreamPublisher`. This seems a bit redundant - each
data package defines its own `NewEventBusConfig` and `NewStreamPublisher`. But t
hat\'s not necessarily a violation.\n\nThe key architecture issue I\'m seeing is
that `internal/biz/wapi/mixing.go`, `internal/biz/wapi/market.go`, `internal/biz
/wcity/wcc/building_map.go`, and `internal/server/wcore/wcc/event_dispatch_serve
r.go` all directly import `internal/pkg/eventbus` and use concrete types like `e
ventbus.StreamPublisher` and `eventbus.EventAdapter`.\n\nIn a typical Kratos/Cle
an Architecture:\n- The `biz` layer should define interfaces for its dependencie
s. It should not depend on `pkg/eventbus`.\n- The `data` layer or `service` laye
r should implement/adapt those interfaces.\n\nHowever, `eventbus.StreamPublisher
` is an interface. The biz layer depends on that interface. Is that a violation?
It depends on project conventions. If `internal/pkg/eventbus` is considered a sh
ared domain package, it might be OK. But usually, `pkg` is for infrastructure/ut
ilities, and `biz` should not depend on it.\n\nWait, looking at the existing cod
e before this PR, the biz layer already imports things like `"new-world/pkg/worl
dgrpc/client"` which is also a `pkg`. So this project might not strictly follow 
the "biz doesn\'t depend on pkg" rule. But `worldgrpc/client` is more of a clien
t/ports layer.\n\nLet me check if there\'s a `repo` interface for event publishi
ng that should be used instead.',
    encrypted=None
)
