ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='I can see the diff for the eventbus and biz files. The eventbus adapt
er has a clear issue: `data, _ := proto.Marshal(payload)` ignores the error. Tha
t\'s a problem - if proto.Marshal fails, it will publish a nil payload event.\n\
nAlso, in biz files, I see they are injecting `eventbus.StreamPublisher` directl
y into the use cases. According to Kratos architecture (which this project seems
to follow), the Biz layer should not depend on infrastructure details. The event
bus is an infrastructure concern. The Biz layer should define its own interface 
or use a domain event port, and the implementation should be in the data/service
layer.\n\nWait, the architecture compliance check says "无跨层调用" and "Biz→Rep
o→Data". If `internal/pkg/eventbus` is considered an infrastructure package, the
n Biz depending on it might be an architecture violation. But `internal/pkg/even
tbus` could be considered a shared package. Still, typically in Kratos:\n- Biz l
ayer depends on Repo interfaces defined in `internal/biz/repo`\n- Service layer 
depends on Biz use cases\n- Data layer implements Repo interfaces\n\nIf Biz dire
ctly uses `eventbus.StreamPublisher`, that\'s a direct dependency on an infrastr
ucture-like component. However, looking at the code, `eventbus.StreamPublisher` 
is an interface defined in `internal/pkg/eventbus/publisher.go`. The PR descript
ion says "集成 MixingUseCase 事件发布". \n\nFor architecture compliance, the key
question is: does Biz define its own event port interface, or does it import `in
ternal/pkg/eventbus`? If it imports `internal/pkg/eventbus`, that\'s likely a vi
olation because `internal/pkg` is infrastructure/shared, and Biz should not depe
nd on it directly. The correct approach would be to define an event publisher in
terface in `internal/biz/repo` or similar, and have the data layer or service la
yer provide the implementation.\n\nBut I need to check the actual publisher inte
rface and how it\'s wired. Let me read the key files.',
    encrypted=None
)
