yer importing biz is correct. Server depends on Biz. But the problem is Biz depe
nding on pkg.\n\nWait, let me re-check the architecture rules:\n- Data → Repo in
terfaces (defined in Biz)\n- Biz → Repo interfaces\n- Service → Biz\n- Server → 
Service\n\nIn Kratos standard layout:\n- `internal/biz` depends on `internal/biz
/repo`\n- `internal/data` implements `internal/biz/repo` and depends on `pkg/...
`\n- `internal/service` depends on `internal/biz`\n- `internal/server` depends o
n `internal/service`\n\nIf `internal/biz` imports `internal/pkg/eventbus`, that\
's a downward dependency (Biz → Infra), which violates the dependency rule.\n\nH
owever, `eventbus.StreamPublisher` is an interface. Some might argue that depend
ing on an interface from a lower layer is acceptable if it\'s a "shared kernel".
But in strict Clean Architecture, even interface definitions should be in the do
main/biz layer or a dedicated ports layer.\n\nGiven the review requirements expl
icitly say "无跨层调用" and "Biz→Repo→Data", I should flag this as an architectu
re violation.\n\nBut wait - the PR only adds the eventbus dependency to existing
